36
00:02:53.659 --> 00:03:00.080
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So I think I, there's, there's different, um, opinions are mixed.

37
00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:06.020
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Which, I, you know, okay, so I think it's important to note that I do not think the all criticism of this film is misogynist.

38
00:03:06.020 --> 00:03:06.500
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: It's not.

39
00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:11.599
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: There are, I get some of the some of the criticism that some people are saying.

40
00:03:11.599 --> 00:03:25.159
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: In particular, the thing I do agree with most people on is that the film is quite kind of dull and gray and not particularly colourful, which is particularly frustrating considering the comic book series that this was based on was a very vibrant one.

41
00:03:25.219 --> 00:03:27.199
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So I do get that.

42
00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:26.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

43
00:03:27.199 --> 00:03:29.120
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I understand that, and I agree with that.

44
00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.002
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I would have been nicer for it to be more viable.

45
00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:32.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

46
00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:36.539
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Some people not really vibing with how the story works and stuff like that.

47
00:03:36.539 --> 00:03:37.439
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That's fair.

48
00:03:37.439 --> 00:03:39.120
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I personally really liked it.

49
00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:41.219
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I thought it was a really good film.

50
00:03:41.219 --> 00:03:45.120
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I liked what they did with the story.

51
00:03:45.120 --> 00:03:46.680
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I liked the characters.

52
00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:49.080
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think Millie Alcock as Supergirl is really good.

53
00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:49.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm.

54
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:54.900
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think it's kind of nicely kind of building on the universe a bit, right?

55
00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:56.819
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I enjoyed Superman last year.

56
00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:56.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

57
00:03:56.819 --> 00:04:00.599
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I thought it was nice to have like a hopeful film for once.

58
00:04:00.599 --> 00:04:18.300
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I think this does a similar sort of thing while not trying to be exactly the same because obviously the thing about Supergirl is that she is, she grew up, well, in the comic books, she grew up on Krypton and it is complicated stuff, but in this film, it's not quite the same.

59
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:01.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Okay.

60
00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:34.800
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: She grows up in Argo City after Krypton has been destroyed, but the point is she still grows up through with Krypton culture, knowing people knowing her family and then seeing everyone die as she goes away to Earth, which is not something that Clark has to do.

61
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:27.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

62
00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:33.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

63
00:04:34.800 --> 00:04:37.500
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: He is a baby when he lands on earth.

64
00:04:37.500 --> 00:04:38.399
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So he doesn't know that.

65
00:04:38.399 --> 00:04:39.240
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: He doesn't experience that.

66
00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:43.379
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Not to say that that can't be grief in of itself, but it's different, right?

67
00:04:41.500 --> 00:04:42.579
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

68
00:04:42.759 --> 00:04:44.439
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yes.

69
00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:47.939
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And so she's never going to be exactly the same.

70
00:04:47.939 --> 00:04:50.040
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: She's always going to have different struggles, blah, blah, blah, blah.

71
00:04:50.040 --> 00:05:03.180
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But I think they did a really good job of still trying to be hopeful even with that difficulty and kind of showing you how she becomes Supergirl and accepts that kind of status, if you will.

72
00:05:03.180 --> 00:05:04.800
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think they did that really nicely.

73
00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:04.459
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

74
00:05:04.800 --> 00:05:07.259
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: It's not like she's completely gone, oh, I'm fine now.

75
00:05:07.259 --> 00:05:10.740
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: You know, you know, but still, I think they did a really good job of that.

76
00:05:10.180 --> 00:05:12.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

77
00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:13.319
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So I really enjoyed it.

78
00:05:13.319 --> 00:05:16.439
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: and I look forward to watching it again.

79
00:05:16.439 --> 00:05:22.259
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think it's going to be interesting because so Rona watches most superhero stuff with me now.

80
00:05:22.259 --> 00:05:24.480
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I've made her watch almost all the DC and Marvel stuff.

81
00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:33.240
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And so she really liked the CW Supergirl show.

82
00:05:24.500 --> 00:05:25.339
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Okay.

83
00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:32.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

84
00:05:33.240 --> 00:05:36.600
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But the thing about that one is that Supergirl is basically just Superman, right?

85
00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:37.399
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

86
00:05:36.600 --> 00:05:40.199
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like, yeah, she has the same backstory, but she doesn't have any of the complications that come with that.

87
00:05:40.199 --> 00:05:44.579
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So it's like her personality is basically just Superman, which is fine for what it was.

88
00:05:44.579 --> 00:05:46.860
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I really like that interpretation as well.

89
00:05:46.860 --> 00:05:47.759
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: It's just it's different.

90
00:05:47.759 --> 00:05:52.980
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So I was a little bit like, ooh, is Ron actually going to like this version of Supergirl?

