00:05:52.980 --> 00:05:56.459
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Because like, you know, she gets drunk and she's angry and blah, blah, blah.

92
00:05:56.459 --> 00:05:58.199
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But actually, I think the way that it's done.

93
00:05:58.199 --> 00:06:00.720
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think she's going to really like what they do with her.

94
00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:00.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

95
00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:08.699
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Um, so I'm really uh, excited to see, um, what she thinks of that when we watch it.

96
00:06:08.699 --> 00:06:16.620
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And as always with these things, I'm, you know, looking at them going, oh, I'll look forward to showing that to Craig in 4 years time.

97
00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:17.899
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

98
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:18.540
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Or whatever.

99
00:06:18.540 --> 00:06:26.220
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So yeah, I think I, as I, as I was saying, I understand some of the criticisms, I do think that some of the criticisms are misogynistic.

100
00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:30.899
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like I saw, um, I saw a, someone trying to, it was perfect.

101
00:06:30.899 --> 00:06:35.160
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Let me read you the exact wording of this at the top of this review because it's so stupid.

102
00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:33.980
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Okay.

103
00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:50.040
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So it starts off with Supergirl's failure, like every other female led movie failure will be blamed on misogyny, but I am here to tell you the real reason female led movies don't succeed at the box office because they're made with the idea that the movie is not for men.

104
00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:56.220
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: They go far as to uglify the female lead so she doesn't appeal to the male gaze.

105
00:06:56.220 --> 00:06:58.560
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Now, can we can we eat?

106
00:06:58.560 --> 00:06:59.759
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: There's so many things to talk about here.

107
00:06:59.759 --> 00:07:05.639
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: First of all, I love the fact of being like, oh, we're not misogynist and then immediately be misogynist.

108
00:07:05.639 --> 00:07:07.079
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Right?

109
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:07.019
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

110
00:07:07.019 --> 00:07:08.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

111
00:07:07.079 --> 00:07:09.899
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like, oh, it's a it's because she's ugly.

112
00:07:09.899 --> 00:07:11.879
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That's misogynistic.

113
00:07:11.879 --> 00:07:12.540
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: are you doing?

114
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:12.959
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yep.

115
00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:13.800
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Two.

116
00:07:13.800 --> 00:07:15.420
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Um, no, she's not.

117
00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.819
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: What are you talking about?

118
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:16.600
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

119
00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:19.000
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

120
00:07:17.819 --> 00:07:20.040
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Are we looking at the same person?

121
00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:21.300
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: What, what?

122
00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:22.579
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

123
00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:26.279
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I sent this review to Ronan, she was like, is she ugly?

124
00:07:22.759 --> 00:07:24.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: That.

125
00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:28.560
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I'm like, no, what?

126
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.439
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: No.

127
00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:32.759
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Three, even if she was, so what?

128
00:07:32.759 --> 00:07:36.420
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Do you have to be attracted to someone to care about them?

129
00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:40.139
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That's what that tells me about you and I'm really worried about you as a human being.

130
00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:39.660
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yep.

131
00:07:39.660 --> 00:07:41.639
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

132
00:07:41.639 --> 00:07:48.839
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: That like a story would not be interesting if the person, like any story is not interesting if the person is not attractive.

133
00:07:48.839 --> 00:07:52.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: That's like, ooh, big yikes.

134
00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:49.839
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Yes.

135
00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:59.040
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So yeah, I do think there are, as with always, uh, you know, people who are being misogynistic about it.

136
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:00.839
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I don't think everyone is.

137
00:08:00.839 --> 00:08:07.500
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: There are, you know, quite a lot of, uh, film reviewers that I follow who I understand what they're saying.

138
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:01.959
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

139
00:08:07.500 --> 00:08:10.079
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I don't get it fully.

140
00:08:10.079 --> 00:08:17.879
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I don't know why they, I'm not really understanding what it is they don't like about the film other than the like visual direction, which I totally get.

141
00:08:17.879 --> 00:08:21.540
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Um, but I'm not saying they're wrong about that.

142
00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:18.899
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

143
00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:24.060
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: They're just like, I disagree.

144
00:08:24.060 --> 00:08:30.480
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I don't I don't really get their their point there, but that's, you know, different things are not everyone, not everything's going to click with everyone.

145
00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:35.460
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I'm a little bit sad that people haven't enjoyed this as much, but I think I very much enjoy it.

146
00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:34.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

147
00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:40.860
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And most of the people who I respect have been saying, I don't like it.

148
00:08:40.860 --> 00:08:42.539
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: A few of them have been saying it's bad.

149
00:08:42.539 --> 00:08:47.159
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That's a whole other conversation, but they all say try it anyway because you might like it, right?

150
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:47.899
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

151
00:08:47.159 --> 00:08:57.539
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I think that is the key difference. I think if you're if you're reading someone's review and they say, it's not for me, they're probably not being misogynistic, right?

152
00:08:50.500 --> 00:08:51.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

153
00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:58.399
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

154
00:08:57.539 --> 00:08:59.759
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Because they're probably like, I didn't like it, but that's fine.

155
00:08:59.759 --> 00:09:02.940
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Whereas the people who are being misogynistic, they'll all be like, it's terrible.

156
00:09:02.940 --> 00:09:03.659
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Don't go see it.

157
00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:05.159
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

158
00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:10.460
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: There's very few films that I will say are actively bad and that people shouldn't go see.

159
00:09:10.460 --> 00:09:14.002
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I actually quite like enjoying bad films sometimes.

160
00:09:14.500 --> 00:09:15.159
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

161
00:09:15.159 --> 00:09:27.100
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: You just have to, it's good to go into it informed sometimes if it is something that is probably going to be bad because you might be in a mood of like, I want to watch good, good cinematography today and it's like, mm, probably shouldn't watch this movie then.

162
00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:21.002
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Yeah.

163
00:09:27.100 --> 00:09:36.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Um, but yeah, that that kind of attitude is just like...

164
00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:28.002
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Yeah.

165
00:09:34.500 --> 00:09:36.600
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: We, we have to get this every single time.

166
00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:40.019
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I don't think that all of the problems with female led movies are because of misogyny.

167
00:09:40.019 --> 00:09:40.679
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Absolutely not.

168
00:09:40.500 --> 00:09:41.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Right.

169
00:09:40.980 --> 00:09:43.799
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Captain Marvel made a $1000000000, right?

170
00:09:43.799 --> 00:09:49.139
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like, it's not as simple as saying people are misogynistic and therefore they don't succeed.

171
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:44.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Right.

172
00:09:49.139 --> 00:09:50.820
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: They can, and they have.

173
00:09:50.820 --> 00:09:56.879
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But it is just, it is another one of those things where it's like when you have conversations about bigotry.

174
00:09:57.360 --> 00:10:05.879
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: People love to like flatten it down into, oh, well, this thing is successful, therefore there's no bigotry and you're like, but that's not how that works, right?

175
00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:06.340
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Nope.

176
00:10:05.879 --> 00:10:12.059
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like, you, you, you know, Barack Obama becoming president and people going, oh, there's no racism anymore.

177
00:10:12.059 --> 00:10:21.240
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: It's like, no, that's no, like people were and are racist towards Obama, that was something he had to overcome.

178
00:10:21.240 --> 00:10:25.919
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And isn't it amazing that he got to that and we don't need to talk about, whether he was good or bad at the job.

179
00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:26.340
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Right.

180
00:10:25.919 --> 00:10:26.519
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That is not the point.

181
00:10:26.519 --> 00:10:31.019
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But like he managed to overcome those things and still do it and isn't that incredible?

182
00:10:31.019 --> 00:10:33.659
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I would say the same thing about something like Captain Marvel.

183
00:10:33.659 --> 00:10:37.019
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: This film, Supergirl's not going to do well, sadly.

184
00:10:37.019 --> 00:10:44.820
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: But I think it is good personally, and I think that lots of people will enjoy it having watched it.

185
00:10:44.820 --> 00:10:47.399
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And so that is my thing.

186
00:10:47.399 --> 00:10:57.960
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: And I really hope my biggest worry is that they go, oh, well, people don't really care about Supergirl and then they just kind of like write the character out of future stories, which I think would be really sad.

187
00:10:57.960 --> 00:11:14.460
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I think the part of the problem with superhero films just now is that the 1st superhero films in franchises don't tend to do particularly well, it's when you continue doing them and you continue making good films and you make more of them, then they, like the 1st Iron Man,

188
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:11.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

189
00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:17.220
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I mean, it was fine, but it didn't make a lot of money, right?

190
00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:17.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

191
00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:20.460
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like they weren't making lots and lots of money until they did later.

192
00:11:20.879 --> 00:11:24.360
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: until they had, you know, multiple sequels, right?

193
00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:21.899
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

194
00:11:21.899 --> 00:11:23.502
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: I ironed it out, yeah.

195
00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:29.820
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Like, only one, only one of the Marvel films made over 2 billion.

196
00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:35.879
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: Now, a lot of made them made over a billion, but that wasn't like none of them in the 1st phase did until the Avengers, I don't think.

197
00:11:35.879 --> 00:11:44.100
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So obviously you could, you know, there's diminishing returns, now they're getting less and less, but you could argue that's because they're worse, right?

198
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.002
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

199
00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:52.502
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So like the idea that like Superman and Supergirl were going to make a $1000000000 was always ridiculous idea because like people need to be convinced of something.

200
00:11:44.500 --> 00:11:45.340
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

201
00:11:54.000 --> 00:12:10.559
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah, I, we were just talking about this the other day about how it's also, there's also kind of like superhero fatigue that any movie that is quote unquote worth seeing in theatre nowadays, like to us, it seems like to my husband and I,

202
00:12:10.559 --> 00:12:13.799
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: It seems like it's usually one of the Marvel movies.

203
00:12:13.799 --> 00:12:21.480
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Um, with some exceptions being like some of the horror movies that have been coming out recently that have been apparently very good in the theatre.

