<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So if I take the number in 2025 and I take the number in 2019, uh, the 2025 number was 76% of the 2019 number.

231
00:14:36.740 --> 00:14:39.080
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: So there's a 25% gap there.

232
00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:40.220
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: I'm not saying that's nothing.

233
00:14:39.500 --> 00:14:40.220
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Mm-hmm.

234
00:14:40.220 --> 00:14:48.919
<v 9C192306-9A0E-4483-99EF-8228817ABFFE>Al: That is obviously a lot of money, but in terms of like, I think the way that people talk about it makes it sound way worse than that, right?

235
00:14:40.279 --> 00:14:41.899
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Right.

236
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:49.960
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Yeah.

237
00:14:49.960 --> 00:14:56.620
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: And I mean, for myself, I think it's the there haven't been movies that have been appealing to me.

238
00:14:56.620 --> 00:15:08.320
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: So, and I think that that is, because another thing that's been coming out a lot are live action remakes of Disney movies, which I'm not interested in.

