01:13:57.439 --> 01:14:05.840
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: They have a paired wings, like they have all of these thing, antennae, all of these things that are that are pieces that put it together.

1229
01:14:05.840 --> 01:14:10.520
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Um, at least that's what people thought however many years ago.

1230
01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:18.380
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Along with their external mouth parts, they also have compound eyes and antennae.

1231
01:14:18.380 --> 01:14:25.159
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: So compound eyes are, instead of just having a simple, um, ocular device.

1232
01:14:25.159 --> 01:14:43.939
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: that can see in one thing, like one thing at a time, they have eyes that are made up of many, sometimes in some organisms, I want to say like 100s or 1000s of pieces that help make one picture.

1233
01:14:43.939 --> 01:14:51.739
<v A7BCC9D0-ED51-4B67-9AE7-4017FAECDA7E>Codey: Um, so it's compound because it's multiple pieces that make, that can help you make, help them make one picture.

